thread.title: Market's early rise subsides

title: Market's early rise subsides
text:
Mon, Sep 14, 2015, 12:34 PM AEST - Australia Markets close in 3 hrs 26 mins Market's early rise subsides AAP – 4 minutes 39 seconds ago Recommend Print 
The share market's strong early rise has fallen away but gains by most of the big banks have kept it in positive territory. 
The big miners rose sharply in early trade but by noon AEST had fallen back to be relatively steady, with BHP Billiton up one cent at $23.72 while Rio Tinto was down 2.5 cents at $51.975. 
The energy sector was weaker as Oil Search rejected an $11.6 billion takeover bid from giant Woodside, with the suitor down 2.3 per cent, Oil Search down 0.7 per cent and Origin Energy 3.4 per cent lower. 
Three of the big four banks were higher, with Westpac and NAB up 1.6 per cent and ANZ up 0.9 per cent, while Commonwealth was down 1.1 per cent. 
KEY FACTS 
* At 1210 AEST on Monday, the benchmark S&P/ASX200 index was up 17.1 points, or 0.34 per cent, at 5,088.2 points. 
* The broader All Ordinaries index was up 15 points, or 0.29 per cent, at 5,111.3 points. 
* The September share price index futures contract was up 18 points at 5,086 points, with 96,012 contracts traded.
